<!--startscanning-->While some may be disturbed by this low count of anime, this is very normal routine for the anime industry. Two high seasons and two low seasons are par for course. Since in this place, a large majority of our fans are English speakers, please talk only about series that have been released on fansubs. Remember to be sure you have read the spoiler rules! Clearly label what you are spoiling before you use spoiler tags, we don't want to assume what you are spoiling.<br><br>Feel free to create series-specific threads for the series you like, or request one be made complete with series summary, more detailed information, and the like. Ask any questions you want, I will be sure to answer as best as I can. And feel free to correct any mistakes!<br><br>6/16 - FLAG (<a href="http://www.flag20xx.net/">http://www.flag20xx.net/</a>)<br>6/29 - Honey &amp; Clover II (<a href="http://www.hachikuro.net/">http://www.hachikuro.net/</a>)<br>6/29 - Binbou Shimai Monogatari (<a href="http://www.toei-anim.co.jp/tv/binboushimai/">http://www.toei-anim.co.jp/tv/binboushimai/</a>)<br><br>7/01 - Demashita! PowerPuff Girls (<a href="http://www.toei-anim.co.jp/tv/ppgz/">http://www.toei-anim.co.jp/tv/ppgz/</a>)<br>7/01 - Otogi Jushi Akazukin (<a href="http://www.akazukin.konami.jp/">http://www.akazukin.konami.jp/</a>)<br>7/02 - Taiyo no Mokushiroku Special - Nihon Budan (<a href="http://www.wowow.co.jp/anime/taiyo/">http://www.wowow.co.jp/anime/taiyo/</a>)<br>7/02 - Kemonozume Sakaba (<a href="http://www.wowow.co.jp/anime/kemono/">http://www.wowow.co.jp/anime/kemono/</a>)<br>7/02 - Chevalier Special (<a href="http://www.chevalier.tv/">http://www.chevalier.tv/</a>)<br>7/02 - Project BLUE Chikyuu SOS (<a href="http://www.projectblue.jp/">http://www.projectblue.jp/</a>)<br>7/03 - Wa Wa Wa Wappi-chan (none)<br>7/03 - Bokura ga Ita (<a href="http://www.bokuragaita.com/">http://www.bokuragaita.com/</a>)<br>7/06 - Mamotte! Lollipop (<a href="http://shop.kodansha.jp/bc/comics/eizou/#anime">http://shop.kodansha.jp/bc/comics/eizou/#anime</a>)<br>7/07 - Zero no Tsukaima (<a href="http://www.zero-tsukaima.com/">http://www.zero-tsukaima.com/</a>)<br>7/08 - Koi Suru Tenshi Angelique ~Kokoro Mezameru Toki~ (<a href="http://www.gamecity.ne.jp/neoromance/tv/ange/">http://www.gamecity.ne.jp/neoromance/tv/ange/</a>)<br>7/11 - Tonagura! (<a href="http://www.starchild.co.jp/special/tonagra/">http://www.starchild.co.jp/special/tonagra/</a>)<br>7/13 - Chokotto Sister (<a href="http://www.chocosis.com/">http://www.chocosis.com/</a>)<br>7/26 - Innocent Venus (<a href="http://www.innocent-v.com/">http://www.innocent-v.com/</a>)<br>7/?? - Usahana (none)<br>7/?? - N H K ni Youkoso (<a href="http://www.boiledeggs.com/chojin/takimotoinfo5.html">http://www.boiledeggs.com/chojin/takimotoinfo5.html</a>)<br>7/?? - Tsuyokisu (<a href="http://www.tsuyokiss.jp/">http://www.tsuyokiss.jp/</a>)<br>7/?? - Coyote Ragtime Show (<a href="http://www.ufotable.com/coyote/">http://www.ufotable.com/coyote/</a>)<br>7/?? - Night Head Genesis (<a href="http://www.nighthead-genesis.jp/">http://www.nighthead-genesis.jp/</a>)<br>7/?? - Gundam SEED C.E.73 -STARGAZER- (<a href="http://www.seed-stargazer.net/">http://www.seed-stargazer.net/</a>)<br>7/?? - Muteki Kanban Musume (<a href="http://www.onimaruhanten.com/">http://www.onimaruhanten.com/</a>)<br>7/?? - Riri to Kaeru to (Otouto) (<a href="http://www.animax.co.jp/etc/0506battle/award/ani_award.html">http://www.animax.co.jp/etc/0506battle/award/ani_award.html</a>)<br>7/?? - Chevailer (<a href="http://www.chevalier.tv/">http://www.chevalier.tv/</a>)<br><br>Summer 2006 - Masuda Kosuke Gekijo Gag Manga Biyori 2nd set (<a href="http://www.kids-station.com/minisite/gyagumanga/">http://www.kids-station.com/minisite/gyagumanga/</a>)<br>Summer 2006 - Kemonozume (<a href="http://www.wowow.co.jp/anime/kemono/">http://www.wowow.co.jp/anime/kemono/</a>)<br>Summer 2006 - Naikaku Kenryoku Hanzai Kyousei Torishimarikan Zaizen Jotaro (<a href="http://www.comicbunch.com/">http://www.comicbunch.com/</a>)<br><br><br>Summaries:<br><br><span style="font-weight:bold">FLAG</span> - (Mecha) 13 episodes<br><br>In the 21st Century, an war is going on in a small country within Asia. The cameraman, Shirasu Saeko, takes a picture of a flag in the middle of a battlefield. Using this picture and flag as basis for making peace with each other, they are about to reach an agreement when the flag is stolen. As a result, Shirasu Saeko must go and record the activities of the thieves, but it was an easy mission gone wrong.<br><br><span style="font-weight:bold">Honey &amp; Clover II</span> - (Drama, Romance) 13 episodes<br><br>This is the second season of Honey &amp; Clover, a fan-favorite series that follows the lives of students living in an art school. In this second season, the story takes a change - it is now far more serious and dramatic than the last season. Some comedy elements remain, but hearts are rumbling and lives are moving onward, so things must be settled!<br><br><span style="font-weight:bold">Binbo Shimai Monogatari</span> - (Drama, School Life)<br><br>This story is a sad and heartwarming tale of two sisters, Kyo and Asu (15 and 9 years old, respectively). They have been living alone since their mother died and father left a huge debt. They overcome many problems financially, and emotionally with the kindness of those around them.<br><br style="font-weight:bold"><span style="font-weight:bold">Demashita! PowerPuff Girls Z</span> - (Comedy) 52 episodes<br><br>Some of us are familar with the PowerPuff girls. This time, the girls have been anime-fied! It's the same type of story that Powerpuff Girls are.<br><br style="font-weight:bold"><span style="font-weight:bold">Kemonozume Sakaba</span> - (Fantasy, Romance) 1 episode<br><br>A man who is the strongest monster hunter falls in love with a horrible monster. Both belong to families that hate each other. A Romeo and Juliet story with a twist.<br><br><span style="font-weight:bold">Chevalier Special</span> - (Fantasy, Historical) 1 episode<br><br>Just before the french Revolution, Versialles was prosperous. One day at dawn, the dead body of Lia de Beaumon was seen floating in the Seine. The letters PSALMS were carved on her coffin. Her little brother, D'Eon is trying to figure the case out when a terrible history gets reveailed to him.<br><br><span style="font-weight:bold">Project BLUE Chikyuu SOS</span> - (Science Fiction)<br><br>In the year 2000, mankind invents an incredible engine that can have a bullet train travel from Tokyo to New York City in 90 minutes. When the engine was about to be unveiled, the train disappears. But it's not an isolated event, many other disappearances occur in the world. The UN forms an Earth Defense Organization, Labyrinth, in order to find out what is happening, and what terrible secret lies hidden.<br><br><span style="font-weight:bold">Bokura ga Ita</span> - (Romance, School Life)<br><br>This is a manga serialized in a shoujo anime, a story about a young girl named Takahashi Nanami and Yano Motoharu. Despite the fact that Motoharu is popular with all the girls in the school, Nanami does not like him. But destiny forces them together, and what will come of it?<br><br><span style="font-weight:bold">Mamotte! Lollipop</span> - (Comedy, Romance, Magic)<br><br>One day, Nina saw a candy next to her cake and ate it. It turned out to be a magicial item, which turned her into an object in an Exam for Magicians. The person who obtains Nina and keeps her for 6 months will become an wizard. Her life becomes chaotic as she gets taken constantly by competitors. <br><br style="font-weight:bold"><span style="font-weight:bold">Zero no Tsukaima</span> - (Adventure, Comedy, Fantasy, Romance) 13 episodes<br><br>Hiraga Saito, an ordinary high schooler, got summoned to another world by the witch Louise. Louise is cute and well known for her inability to actually use magic properly. When Louise tricks him into kissing her, Hiraga Saito becomes her familiar. As an result, he has to live with Louise in the dorms of the Magic Academy she attends. Painful adventures begin!<br><br><span style="font-weight:bold">Koi Suru Tenshi Angelique ~Kokoro Mezameru Toki~</span> - (Adventure, Fantasy)<br><br>Angelique is a dating simulation game for girls, like Meine Liebe and Harukanaru Toki no Naka de. The story revolves around two girls who were selected from different planets to protect the universe. In order to become the sole protector of the universe, they must go through many trails to test their worth. They have nine guardians of the elements, who help them. But the girls find themselves noticing feelings for the guardians who help them, will they choose to fall in love or to protect the universe?<br><br><span style="font-weight:bold">Tonagura!</span> - (Romance) 13 episodes<br><br>Kazuki and Yuji were childhood friends, but Yuji had to leave for 10 years. When Kazuki finds out he is coming back, she is anticipating what kind of man he has become. Despite her illusions, he turns out to be a dirty pervert who is trying to win her love (or body?) Will Kazuki open up to him, or is he just a dirty pervert after all? <br><br><span style="font-weight:bold">Chokotto Sister</span> - (Romance)<br><br>When Haruma was a child, he wished for a younger sister for Christmas. Years later, Santa gives him a little sister (It took years to make the little sister, apparently). Suprised by this gift, he takes her in and names her Chokotto. She is very cute and is the little sister he dreamed to have. A very cute story.<br><br><span style="font-weight:bold">Innocent Venus</span> - (Mecha, Science Fiction)<br><br>In 2010, hurricanes pop up all over the world and 6 billion people lose their lives. As a result, the earth has changed so much the map must be completely redrawn. Japan survived and recovered a bit thanks to technology they have been researching for a long time. However, the rich and poor are now separated, and a special military squad was created in order to keep the rich and poor from breaking out into a war. <br><br><span style="font-weight:bold">NHK ni Youkoso</span> - (Comedy)<br><br>The story revolves around an hikkikomori, something often associated with being otaku despite that it's a far bigger stigma, named Sato Tatsuhiro. Due to paranoia, he thinks his becoming a hikkikomori is a result of an evil group called Nihon Hikikomori Kyokai (NHK) so he deciedes to fight back. After finally leaving his house, Nakahari Misaki shows up in his life and tries to change his life. Very funny and sad.<br><br><span style="font-weight:bold">Tsuyokisu</span> - (Harem, School Life) 13 episodes<br><br>In this bishoujo game to anime adaptation, you are surrounded by tsundere girls. Tsundere girls are girls who are strict and uptight in public, not allowing anyone to see their true self. But sometimes get caught in weak moments where they show their soft and childish side.<br><br>The main characer, Tsushima Reo is in love with one such character, but there are quite a few others going after him. Which one would he choose?<br><br><span style="font-weight:bold">Coyote Ragtime Show</span> - (Action, Science Fiction)<br><br>A war is occuring on the planet of Grazeland, but because the other planets are worried the war might break out in other planets, they deciede to destroy the planet of Grazeland. There are seven days left before it's destroyed, but there is a pirate treasure left by the Pirate King, Gol D. Roger... er no, sorry, by a guy named Blues on the planet, and people want to recover it before the world is destroyed!<br><br style="font-weight:bold"><span style="font-weight:bold">Gundam SEED C.E.73 -STARGAZER-</span> - (Mecha, Science Fiction) 3 episodes<br><br>Another continuation to the Gundam franchise.<br><br style="font-weight:bold"><span style="font-weight:bold">Muteki Kanban Musume</span> - (Comedy) 12 episodes<br><br>A Kanban Musume is a poster girl for a store. This is what Onimaru Miki is, for her families Chinese restaurant. But she always makes trouble for everyone! There is another kanban musume, Kannazuki Megumi, for a bakery store. Megumi acts cute and nice, but it's just a disguise. Megumi considers Miki an rival, and keeps picking fights with her!<br><br style="font-weight:bold"><span style="font-weight:bold">Riri to Kaeru to (Otouto)</span> - (Adventure, Fantasy)<br><br>This is a story of Riri, who went to an amusement park. Within the park, there is a place called Frog Castle, where she drew a sword. If she beats a snake with her sword, the Frog King will grant her any wish. But she must face some trails before then!<br><br style="font-weight:bold"><span style="font-weight:bold">Chevalier</span> - (Fantasy, Historical) 24 episodes<br><br>Just before the french Revolution, Versialles was prosperous. One day at dawn, the dead body of Lia de Beaumon was seen floating in the Seine. The letters PSALMS were carved on her coffin. Her little brother, D'Eon is trying to figure the case out when a terrible history gets reveailed to him.<br><br><span style="font-weight:bold">Kemonozume</span> - (Romance, Fantasy) 13 episodes<br><br>A man who is the strongest monster hunter falls in love with a horrible monster. Both belong to families that hate each other. A Romeo and Juliet story with a twist.<br><br><span style="font-weight:bold">Naikaku Kenryoku Hanzai Kyousei Torishimarikan Zaizen Jotaro</span> - (Drama) 13 episodes<br><br>The story revolves around Zaizen Jotaro, an investigator who is able to use illegal means in order to find which politicians and businessmen are abusing their power and wealth for evil means and bring them to justice.<br><br><!--/startscanning-->

